tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,
context: Pregnancy Exercise,Pre and Post Delivery Care,Gynae Problems,Family Planning,
review: We had been consulting Dr. Ranjana ever since we planned our pregnancy and we are glad we took this decision. Her advice and medication has been extremely beneficial through out the period. Any words of appreciation will be less for the kind of advice, strength and support that she has provided us in all these months. Not only is she an expert in her area but is also very approachable, friendly and patient. She has always been available and responded to all our queries even in the wee hours. She goes an extra mile to understand the problems of her patients and provides the best solution. Our pregnancy wasn't a very smooth one but Dr. Ranjana ensured we were calmed down every time we panicked. Even during the delivery process she was available at all times and ensured that the baby was delivered safely without causing any risk to the mother or the baby. On 16th of October 2020 we were blessed with a baby boy and we are thankful to Dr. Ranjana as it wouldn't have been possible without her support. we would definitely recommend Dr. Ranjana to all the future parents to be.
reply_text: Thank you so much.... it's you who keep me going üôè

review: I have been consulting Dr. Ranjana Tibrewal for almost 1.5 yrs now as a PCOS patient. The experience have been really great with her. The way she explains the problems and treatment options is easy and understandable and as a patient I think it is very important for me to have some knowledge about my disease so that I can take proper care of myself. *** ********* ********** ** *** **** ****** ** **** *** ** *** I am doing pretty good at present.

tags: Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: My wife had taken a video consultation with the doctor two days back. Chief complaints were irregular menstrual cycle , inflammation and vag itching due to infection. The doctor prescribed blood tests and asked for clinic visit. ** **** ********* **** *** ******** ********* *** ****** ******** ** **** ** ******* *** ******** *** ******* **** ** ****** ******No medicine at all. ***** **** ** *** **** ** ***** * ****** *** ******** ********* * ****** ******** ******* ***** What‚Äôs the point of video consultation if we have to visit clinic for getting medicine. We paid 800 bucks for nothing. ****** ***** **** ******** * * ******* *** ** *** *********** ** ********* ****** ** ********* ********* Not recommended at all!!!!
reply_text:
As per Online Consultation Guidelines framed by Govt of India, one can prescribe online medications ONLY with a  diagnosis of reasonable surety  based on a "good patient history " . With inconsistent symptoms  which are open to many causes, blind prescription of medication online is NOT allowed. 
Patients need to understand that Online Consultation is NOT  SUBSTITUTE to chamber consultation and clinical examination  is  sometimes an essential prerequisite to  prescribing medicines. Moreover, prescribing any ointment based on vague symptoms is NOT GOOD OR ETHICAL PRACTICE. 
Hence the patient comment on a doctor's experience or confidence without proper knowledge of the subject shows her immaturity. 
Anyway , I wish you all the best for the future

review: Overall i dont have any personal grudge to burst out for, *** ****** ** ******* ***** ** ***** * **** *** ******* *** ** ************* ** *** ***** ** ******* ******* *** ****** ** ****** I consulted Dr. Rajana on 5th feb 2022 which i found to be a bad judgement call *** ** ******* ******** ******** My wife and myself had some queries to which we visited her and she didnt let her speak at all he was so confident that she was least bothered to even check our previous reports and bluntly gave abrut lectures which is of no use. I am currently staying in Bangalore and i have never faced such unprofessionalism from any doctor yet. The way he did the scanning of my wife was horrible to which she scared her to the brim. **** ****** ** *** ** **** *** *** **** ********* ***** *** ****** ****** *** ** *** **** **** ************* ***** *** ********** In short i wouldnt recommend Dr. Ranjana to anyone because of her attitude. This is not something i am paying to write but out of my own experience. Also, i visited her in Apollo clinic in Kolkata which is not mentioned here in Practo which is a weird thing to note.
reply_text:
I am relying today , rather late, because one of my patients insisted that I should reply- because what is described  here is completely opposite to my behavior. I ALWAYS give a detailed hearing to my patient , infact my consultation often runs over 30 mts ...
Secondly , I do NOT perform SCANS in chamber , never have. So this particular "scanning " issue cannot be true... maybe you are confusing with someone else totally....
Also, ALL my patients review from their personal experience... any other insinuation would be insulting your co - patients.
Thank you and all the best to you.
